SIMPLE: importune
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Importune
<hw>Im`por*tune"</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧m`p⟦ocr⟧r*t⟦umac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>importun</ets>, L. <ets>importunus</ets>; pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + a derivative from the root of <ets>portus</ets>
harbor, <ets>importunus</ets> therefore orig. meaning, hard of access.
See <er>Port</er> harbor, and cf. <er>Importunate</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Inopportune; unseasonable.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Troublesome; vexatious; persistent; urgent; hence,
vexatious on account of untimely urgency or pertinacious
solicitation.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And their <qex>importune</qex> fates all satisfied.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of all other affections it [envy] is the most <qex>importune</qex>
and continual.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Importune</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Importune
<hw>Im`por*tune"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Importuned</conjf> <pr>(⟦icr⟧m`p⟦ocr⟧r*t⟦umac⟧nd")</pr>; <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Importuning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From
<er>Importune</er>, <pos>a.</pos>: cf. F. <ets>importuner</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To request or solicit, with urgency; to press with
frequent, unreasonable, or troublesome application or pertinacity;
hence, to tease; to irritate; to worry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their ministers and residents here have perpetually
<qex>importuned</qex> the court with unreasonable demands.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To import; to signify.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧It <xex>importunes</xex> death.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Importune</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Importune
<hw>Im`por*tune"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To require; to
demand.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We shall write to you,⟦br⟧
As time and our concernings shall <qex>importune</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Importunely</ent>⟦br⟧
